If he read it properly off the bat, he'd have caught it standing upright.

Commentary: wide yorker, stabs this to backward point, Brathwaite with a sharp catch diving forward! But wait. There's drama! The batsman stands his ground claiming it was a bump ball driven into the pitch. Replays clearly show he hit this on the half-volley and it came straight into the air. Definitely not a bump ball, and a clean catch too. Rutherford has to begrudgingly walk off. Dhani knew immediately it was a clean wicket and celebrated wildly when Brathwaite took the catch.
